<DOC><DOCNO> AP890928-0092 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-28-89 1244EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-France-PrisonRiot     09-28 0140</FIRST><SECOND>AM-France-Prison Riot,0142</SECOND><HEAD>Riot Police Retake Prison in Southern France</HEAD><DATELINE>DRAGUIGNAN, France (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hundreds of riot police armed withtear gas took control of a prison in southern France on Thursdayafter a night of rioting by inmates protesting prison conditions,police said.   Prisoners offered no resistence when about 400 police enteredthe jail at 7:45 a.m. and ordered the inmates back to their cells,according to police.   Calm was restored within 45 minutes.   The rioting occurred during a strike by prison guards, who aredemanding higher wages. About 200 prisoners trashed cells, burnedbeds and climbed on the roof to protest conditions and thedisruption of visiting schedules caused by the strike.   Tension is said to be high in many of the country's 180 prisons.Union officials say guards are on strike in about 70 of them.</TEXT></DOC>